      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LAVENDER LANE (6) hit the frame on debut then last start flew the lids and led throughout to get off the mark with maiden win, scoring by 2.25 lengths at this track over 530m (31.05). Showing good promise and looks a key player again. HANDOVER (1) finished in the minors last time but the start prior broke the clock when winning over 531m at Gawler, taking a Grade 6 in a strong 30.90. Has the ability and can find winning form again. ADHANA ANNIE (2) stalked the lead and fought on well to finish 5 lengths away in second (20.16) at this track in a Grade 6 over 342m. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings three times from four starts. Hard to beat again. WEBLEC PEBBLES (3) recorded a 5 length win (25.82) in a Grade 6 last time at Murray Bridge. Already a winner from this draw.",
